otballbox collapsible\n|bg=eeeeee\n|date = 21 August 2012\n|time = \n|team1 = '''Garhwal Heros\n|score = 1\u20132\n|aet =\n|report = [http://www.kolkatafootballs.com/durand_cup_2012/preliminary.html Report]\n|team2 = [[FC Punjab Police|Punjab Police]]\n|goals1 = [[Alihassan Bala|Bala]] {{goal|80}}\n|goals2 = [[Harjinder Singh (footballer)|Singh]] {{goal|52}}<br>[[Vijay Kumar (footballer)|Kumar]] {{goal|65}}\n|stadium = [[Ambedkar Stadium]], [[New Delhi]]\n|attendance = \n|referee = \n|stack=yes\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date = 21 August 2012\n|time = \n|team1 = Assam Rifles\n|score = 3\u20130\n|aet =\n|report = [http://www.kolkatafootballs.com/durand_cup_2012/preliminary.html Report]\n|team2 = '''JCT Academy'''\n|goals1 = [[Ajit Kumar Singh (footballer)|Singh]] {{goal|7||53}}<br>[[M. Kamei|Kamei]] {{goal|33}}\n|goals2 = \n|stadium = [[Ambedkar Stadium]], [[New Delhi]]\n|attendance = \n|referee = \n|stack=yes\n}}\n\n==Quarter-Finals==\n{{main article|2012 Durand Cup Quarter-Finals}}\nThe Quarter-Finals of the Durand Cup shall be played between 12 teams. Five of the teams currently play in [[2012\u201313 I-League]], two played in the [[2012 I-League 2nd Division]] and one currently play in the [[Mumbai Football League]]. The other four spots would have been taken up by the top three teams from the preliminary round plus one service team. However, on 22 August 2012 it was announced that [[Hindustan Aeronautics Limited S.C.|HAL SC]] would withdraw from the tournament (along with [[Churchill Brothers S.C.]] who withdrew before the initial list of teams was released) and thus freeing an extra space. So in order to fill it up the Durand Football Committee decided to qualify the four teams remaining in the preliminary rounds.<ref name=DurandSponsor>{{cite web|last=Basu|first=Indranil|title=Durand gets sponsor but Churchill pull out|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-08-22/top-stories/33321844_1_durand-football-tournament-society-durand-cup-new-sponsors|work=Times of India|accessdate=22 August 2012}}</ref> Therefore, [[Delhi United FC]], [[FC Punjab Police]], Assam Rifles FC, and CRPF FC will qualify directly for the Quarter-Finals.<ref name=DurandSponsor/>\n\n{{col-start}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Group A===\n{{:2012 Durand Cup Quarter-Finals|transcludesection=Group A}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Group B===\n{{:2012 Durand Cup Quarter-Finals|transcludesection=Group B}}\n{{col-end}}\n{{col-start}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Group C===\n{{:2012 Durand Cup Quarter-Finals|transcludesection=Group C}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Group D===\n{{:2012 Durand Cup Quarter-Finals|transcludesection=Group D}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Semi-Finals==\n{{footballbox collapsible\n| bg=eeeeee\n| date = 30 August 2012\n| time = 16:00 IST\n| team1 = [[Air India FC|Air India]]\n| score = 2\u20132\n|aet=yes\n| penaltyscore = 7\u20136\n| report = [http://www.dailypioneer.com/sports/91224-air-india-mumbai-in-final.html Report]\n| team2 = '''[[SESA F.A.|SESA Football Academy]]\n| goals1 = [[Pradeep Mohanraj|Mohanraj]] {{goal|55}}<br>G.Singh {{goal|90+4}}\n| goals2 = S. Singh {{goal|35}}<br>Chukwuma {{goal|44}}\n| stadium = [[Ambedkar Stadium]], [[New Delhi]]\n| attendance = \n| referee = \n| stack = yes\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n| date = 30 August 2012\n| time = 18:00 IST\n| team1 = '''[[Assam Rifles FC|Assam Rifles]]\n| score = 1\u20131\n|aet=yes\n| penaltyscore = 5\u20136\n| report = [http://www.dailypioneer.com/sports/91224-air-india-mumbai-in-final.html Report]\n| team2 = [[Dodsal FC|Dodsal]]\n| goals1 = Kamei {{goal|72}}\n| goals2 = Kumar {{goal|80}}\n| stadium = [[Ambedkar Stadium]], [[New Delhi]]\n| attendance = \n| referee = \n| stack = yes\n}}\n\n==Final==\n{{main article|2012 Durand Cup Final}}\n\n{{footballbox collapsible\n| date = 1 September 2012\n| time = 18:30 IST\n| team1 = [[Air India FC|Air India]]\n| score = 0\u20130\n|aet=yes\n| report = [http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/football/top-stories/Air-India-win-Durand-Cup/articleshow/16160571.cms Report]\n| team2 = '''[[Dodsal F.C.|Dodsal]]\n| goals1 = \n| goals2 = \n|penalties1=[[Pradeep Mohanraj|Mohanraj]] {{pengoal}}<br>[[Vijith Shetty|Shetty]] {{pengoal}}<br>[[Harshad Meher|Meher]] {{penmiss}}<br>Chaudhari {{penmiss}}<br>[[Ramandeep Singh (footballer)|R. Singh]] {{pengoal}}\n|penaltyscore=3\u20132\n|penalties2={{penmiss}} [[Pappachen Pradeep|Pradeep]]<br>{{pengoal}} Kumar<br>{{pengoal}} Diakhate<br>{{penmiss}} Ghosh<br>{{penmiss}} [[Mohammed Rafi (footballer)|Rafi]]\n| stadium = [[Ambedkar Stadium]], [[New Delhi]]\n| attendance =\n| referee = \n| stack = yes\n}}\n\n==Scorers==\n''All goals from tournament proper. Goals from qualifiers are not counted in this list.''\n{{col-begin}}\n{{Col-2}}\n;3 goals\n* {{flagicon|IND}} M. Kamei ([[Assam Rifles FC|Assam Rifles]])\n\n;2 goals\n* {{flagicon|NGA}} Michael Okwudiu ([[Delhi United FC|Delhi United]])\n* {{flagicon|IND}} [[Mohammed Rafi (footballer)|Mohammed Rafi]] ([[Dodsal FC|Dodsal]])\n* {{flagicon|IND}} [[Thoi Singh]] ([[Dodsal FC|Dodsal]])\n* {{flagicon|IND}} [[Pappachen Pradeep]] ([[Dodsal FC|Dodsal]])\n* {{flagicon|IND}} Sunil Kumar ([[Dodsal FC|Dodsal]])\n* {{flagicon|NGA}} [[Ogba Kalu Nnanna]] ([[Sporting Clube de Goa|Sporting Goa]])\n* {{flagicon|IND}} [[Pradeep Mohanraj]] ([[Air India FC|Air India]])\n* {{flagicon|NGA}} Chukwudi Chukwuma ([[SESA F.A.|SESA Football Academy]])\n\n;1 goal\n* {{flagicon|IND}} [[Jeje Lalpekhlua]] ([[Pune F.C.|Pune]])\n* {{flagicon|IND}} [[Holicharan Narzary]] ([[Pailan Arrows]])\n* {{flagicon|IND}} [[Milan Singh]] ([[Pailan Arrows]])\n* {{flagicon|IND}} [[Avinabo Bag]] ([[Pailan Arrows]])\n* {{flagicon|IND}} [[Souvik Chakraborty]] ([[Air India FC|Air India]])\n* {{flagicon|CMR}} [[Bong Bertrand]] ([[Sporting Clube de Goa|Sporting Goa]])\n* {{flagicon|IND}} [[Victorino Fernandes]] ([[Sporting Clube de Goa|Sporting Goa]])\n* {{flagicon|IND}} [[Pratesh Shirodkar]] ([[Sporting Clube de Goa|Sporting Goa]])\n* {{flagicon|IND}} [[Kailash Patil]] ([[ONGC F.C.|ONGC]])\n* {{flagicon|IND